The paper presents an algorithm for training recurrent neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The proposed approach is specifically designed to handle input sequences of varying lengths, which is a common problem in tasks such as online handwriting recognition (cs.CV, cs.CL). The use of multiple graphical processing units for data parallelization is also a relevant topic in computer science (cs.NE).
